msgstr "Notre flippomètre vous permet de partager votre opinion. Lisez la critique du produit, puis évaluez à quel point vous pensez que le produit est effrayant ou non, et à quel point vous seriez susceptible de l’acheter. Cliquez sur voter pour voir comment votre opinion se compare aux autres."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:68
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Can it snoop on me?"
msgid "Can it snoop on me?"
msgstr "Ce produit peut-il m’espionner ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:70
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Just because a device has a camera, microphone, or tracks location doesn’t mean it will snoop on you. It simply means it <em>could</em> and you should be aware of that. Also, many connected devices are controlled by apps on your phone. The apps often ask to use the phone’s camera, microphone or location tracking. Keep an eye on that, as some of the permissions the apps ask for might surprise you."
msgid "Just because a device has a camera, microphone, or tracks location doesn’t mean it will snoop on you. It simply means it could and you should be aware of that. Also, many connected devices are controlled by apps on your phone. The apps often ask to use the phone’s camera, microphone or location tracking. Keep an eye on that, as some of the permissions the apps ask for might surprise you."
msgstr "Ce n’est pas parce qu’un appareil est équipé d’une caméra, d’un microphone ou d'un système de localisation qu’il vous surveillera. Cela signifie simplement que cela <em>pourrait</em> être le cas et que vous devez en avoir conscience. De plus, de nombreux objets connectés sont contrôlés par des applications sur votre téléphone. Ces applications demandent souvent d’utiliser la caméra, le microphone ou le suivi de localisation du téléphone. Gardez un œil là-dessus, car certaines des autorisations demandées par les applications pourraient vous surprendre."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:81
msgid "What is required to sign up?"
msgstr "Que faut-il pour s’inscrire ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:83
msgid "To use a product do you need to give up your email address, your phone number, or sign in through a third party such as a social media account like Facebook? This is good to know ahead of time so you’re aware of what you’ll need to use the product."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:92
msgid "What data does this product collect?"
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:94
msgid "Connected devices collect information on their users. We look at what personal, biometric, and social data a product is likely to collect on you when you use it. Knowing what sorts of personal information you’ll need to give up to use a product is useful to help understand just how much a company could be learning about you. The more information you give up, the better they may know you. Personal data includes things like name, email address, phone number, gender, age, and date of birth. Biometric data includes things like voice recordings, fingerprint, facial recognition, height, weight, heart rate, sleep data, menstrual cycles, and blood oxygen levels. Social data includes things like your contacts and friends or connections you have through a platform, like gamer friends through a gaming console or connections you have through a fitness app."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:108
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Your voice, heart rate, activity levels, stress levels, sleep patterns, menstrual cycles, even your fingerprint and facial features are some of the most intimate, sensitive data devices can collect on you. You should be aware if a device collects this data and how that data is used after it is collected."
msgid "A note on biometric data. Your voice, heart rate, activity levels, stress levels, sleep patterns, menstrual cycles, even your fingerprint and facial features are some of the most intimate, sensitive data devices can collect on you. You should be aware if a device collects this data and how that data is used after it is collected."
msgstr "Votre voix, votre fréquence cardiaque, vos niveaux d’activité ou de stress, vos habitudes de sommeil, vos cycles menstruels, même vos empreintes digitales et vos traits du visage sont parmi les données les plus intimes et sensibles que les appareils peuvent collecter sur vous. Vous devez savoir si un appareil collecte ces données et comment ces données sont utilisées après leur collecte."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:118
msgid "How does it use this data?"
msgstr "Comment ce produit utilise-t-il les données ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:120
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Nearly every company collects some kind of information on its users. That’s how the internet works. It’s how they use and care for this information that matters. You should know whether a company shares or sells your personal information to others and for what reasons."
msgid "Nearly every company collects some kind of information on its users. That’s how the internet works. It’s how they use and care for this information that matters. You should know whether a company shares or sells your personal information to others and for what reasons. This criteria is one of the criteria we use to determine if a product receives our <em>*Privacy Not Included</em> warning label. Companies that share or sell your data to third parties received a mini-warning label."
msgstr "Presque toutes les entreprises collectent des informations sur leurs utilisateurs. C’est ainsi que fonctionne Internet. Ce qui importe c’est la manière dont elles utilisent et prennent soin de ces informations. Vous devez savoir si une entreprise partage ou vend vos informations personnelles à des tiers et pour quelles raisons."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:132
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:273
msgid "How can you control your data?"
msgstr "Comment pouvez-vous contrôler vos données ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:134
msgid "Companies collect a lot of data on their consumers. Who controls that data? Being able to contact a company and ask them to delete any data they have on you is a very good thing."
msgstr "Les entreprises collectent de nombreuses données sur leurs consommateurs. Qui contrôle ces données ? Pouvoir contacter une entreprise et lui demander de supprimer toutes les données qu’elle détient sur vous est une très bonne chose."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:143
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:286
msgid "What is the company’s known track record of protecting users’ data?"
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:146
msgid "It’s one thing for a company to say they care about their users’ privacy. It’s another thing to show. We looked at the track records of all the companies in the guide dating back to January, 2018 to see if they had known data breaches, security vulnerabilities, or other public privacy missteps. We found concerns ranging from small—an employee accidentally replying to all in an email exposing users email addresses—to large—corporate espionage and data breaches involving millions of users’ data. This criteria is one of the criteria we use to determine if a product receives our <em>*Privacy Not Included</em> warning label. Companies that had multiple or large privacy or security breaches received a mini-warning label."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:157
msgid "*privacy not included with this product"
msgstr "*confidentialité non incluse avec ce produit"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:162
msgid "Can this product be used offline?"
msgstr "Ce produit peut-il être utilisé hors connexion ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:164
msgid "Does every product really need to be connected to the internet to work? What happens if the internet goes out or you just want to use that smart scale as a scale? Some <em>*Privacy Not Included</em> users reached out to us over the past couple of years and asked us to include this in our guide. We aim to please!"
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:174
msgid "User friendly privacy info?"
msgstr "Les informations relatives à la vie privée sont-elles accessibles et compréhensibles ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:176
msgid "Privacy information should be clear, readable, and communicate basic information to consumers about what happens to their data. Privacy policies are often written more for lawyers than consumers. That’s why it’s nice to see more and more companies creating consumer-friendly privacy pages to outline how they handle your personal information and the data they collected on their users. We hope to see this trend continue."
msgstr "Les informations sur le respect de la vie privée doivent être claires, lisibles et communiquer des informations de base aux consommateurs sur ce qui arrive à leurs données. Les politiques de confidentialité sont souvent écrites davantage pour les avocats que pour les consommateurs. C’est pourquoi il est agréable de voir de plus en plus d’entreprises créer des pages de confidentialité conviviales pour décrire comment elles traitent vos informations personnelles et les données qu’elles ont collectées sur leurs utilisateurs. Nous espérons voir cette tendance se poursuivre."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:187
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/why_we_made.html:56
msgid "Our Minimum Security Standards"
msgstr "Nos critères élémentaires de sécurité"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:189
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "We developed a set of minimum security standards we think all connected products should meet at the <em>very</em> least. Think of it as a “you must be this tall to ride” set of standards. These include five basic things: The product must use encryption, the company must provide automatic security updates, if a product uses a password, it must require a strong password, the company must have a way to manage security vulnerabilities found in their products, and the company must have an accessible privacy policy. If you would like to learn more about our minimum security standards, <a href=\"%(url)s\">go here</a>."
msgid "We developed a set of minimum security standards we think all connected products should meet at the very least. Think of it as a “you must be this tall to ride” set of standards. These include five basic things: The product must use encryption, the company must provide automatic security updates, if a product uses a password, it must require a strong password, the company must have a way to manage security vulnerabilities found in their products, and the company must have an accessible privacy policy. If you would like to learn more about our minimum security standards go here."
msgstr "Nous avons développé un ensemble de critères élémentaires de sécurité que nous pensons que tous les objets connectés devraient <em>à tout le moins</em> respecter. Considérez que cette barre est le minimum qu’ils doivent atteindre. Ces critères comprennent cinq éléments de base : le produit doit utiliser un chiffrement, l’entreprise doit fournir des mises à jour de sécurité automatiques, si un produit utilise un mot de passe, il doit exiger un mot de passe fort, l’entreprise doit avoir un moyen de gérer les failles de sécurité trouvées dans ses produits, et l’entreprise doit avoir une politique de confidentialité accessible. Si vous souhaitez en savoir plus sur nos critères élémentaires de sécurité, <a href=\"%(url)s\">rendez-vous ici</a>."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:202
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:135
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/minimum_security.html:45
msgid "Encryption"
msgstr "Chiffrement"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:204
msgid "Encryption is your friend. It protects your private and personal information by scrambling it up into a code so that the only people or machines who can read it are the ones on the other end who have the key to unscramble that code. Products that don’t use encryption send personal information over the internet unscrambled so anyone can see it."
msgstr "Le chiffrement est votre ami. Il protège vos informations privées et personnelles en les brouillant dans un code afin que les seules personnes ou machines qui puissent les lire soient celles de l’autre côté qui ont la clé pour déchiffrer ce code. Les produits qui n’utilisent pas de chiffrement envoient des informations personnelles sur Internet sans être brouillées, de sorte que tout le monde peut les voir."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:214
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:150
msgid "Security updates"
msgstr "Mises à jour de sécurité"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:216
msgid "Sometimes security vulnerabilities are found in products after they are sold to the public. For that reason, companies should have a way to quickly push a security update out to the product automatically so it fixes the security vulnerability without the consumer ever needing to worry about it."
msgstr "Parfois, des failles de sécurité sont détectées dans les produits après leur vente au public. Pour cette raison, les entreprises devraient avoir un moyen de transférer rapidement une mise à jour de sécurité vers le produit afin de corriger la vulnérabilité de sécurité sans que le consommateur ait à s’en préoccuper."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:226
msgid "Strong Password"
msgstr "Mot de passe robuste"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:228
msgid "Remembering passwords might be annoying, but having a good password is still one of the best lines of defense we have when it comes to protecting our privacy and security. It’s great when a password is required. But default passwords that are the same for all consumers and never change can be just as bad. You should be required to change the default password to a strong password. Products with a default password that does not require changing can leave users’ personal information exposed."
msgstr "Se souvenir des mots de passe peut être fastidieux, mais avoir un bon mot de passe reste l’une des meilleures lignes de défense que nous ayons lorsqu’il s’agit de protéger notre vie privée et notre sécurité. C’est bien de demander un mot de passe, mais les mots de passe par défaut qui sont les mêmes pour tous les consommateurs et qui ne changent jamais peuvent être tout aussi mauvais que pas de mot de passe du tout. Le produit doit vous inviter à remplacer le mot de passe par défaut par un mot de passe fort. Les produits qui conservent un mot de passe par défaut sans demander de le changer peuvent laisser les informations personnelles des utilisateurs exposées."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:240
msgid "Manages vulnerabilities"
msgstr "Gestion des vulnérabilités"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:242
#, python-format
msgid "Security vulnerabilities in products happen. It’s how companies manage them when they arise that matter. We looked at whether or not companies have a system in place to manage vulnerabilities in the product when they are found. This includes having a point of contact for reporting vulnerabilities or an equivalent <a href=\"%(url)s\">bug bounty program</a>."
msgstr "Des failles de sécurité dans les produits peuvent toujours arriver. C’est la manière dont les entreprises les gèrent lorsqu’elles surviennent qui importe. Nous avons cherché à savoir si les entreprises avaient ou non un système en place pour gérer les vulnérabilités du produit lorsqu’elles étaient détectées. Cela implique d’avoir un point de contact pour signaler les vulnérabilités ou un <a href=\"%(url)s\">programme de prime aux bogues</a>."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:252
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Privacy policies"
msgid "Privacy policies"
msgstr "Politiques de confidentialité"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:254
msgid "Privacy policies detail a lot of important information about how companies collect, use, and share your personal information. Because of that, this information should be easily found and easily understood."
msgstr "Les politiques de confidentialité contiennent de nombreuses informations importantes sur la manière dont les entreprises collectent, utilisent et partagent vos informations personnelles. Pour cette raison, ces informations doivent être facilement trouvables et compréhensibles."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:263
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:369
msgid "Does the product use AI?"
msgstr "Le produit utilise-t-il une IA ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:265
msgid "More and more products use artificial intelligence these days. It’s not just smart speakers and facial recognition in security cameras either. It’s AI in dog toys and fitness trackers and connected workout equipment. For our reviews, we defined AI as: “Changes are made to the product’s technology continually based on your user data.” What does all this mean for consumers? We’re just starting to understand. However, most consumers don’t know when AI is being used or how it may affect their experience. We believe companies should provide this information to consumers as AI-enabled products become more prevalent."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:279
#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/methodology.html:382
msgid "Does the AI use your personal data to make decisions about you?"
msgstr "L’IA utilise-t-elle vos données personnelles pour prendre des décisions vous concernant ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:281
msgid "We think consumers should know if a product uses their personal data to make decisions for or about them."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:289
msgid "Does the company allow users to see how the AI works?"
msgstr "L’entreprise permet-elle aux utilisateurs d’observer le fonctionnement de l’IA ?"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:291
msgid "One of the biggest issues surrounding artificial intelligence in our consumer products is having access to essential information about how AI-enabled features work. For example, what data does it collect and how does it use that information to make decisions for or about you. Knowing how it works lets users evaluate if there may be a chance of bias or ethical implications they should consider before using a product driven by AI."
msgstr ""

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:302
msgid "Updates"
msgstr "Mises à jour"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:304
msgid "When news breaks or we come across a relevant article about a product in this guide, we will share it in the updates section on each product page."
msgstr "Lorsque des informations sont publiées ou que nous trouvons un article pertinent sur un produit de ce guide, nous le partageons dans la section « Mises à jour » de chaque page de produit."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:312
msgid "Comments"
msgstr "Commentaires"

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:314
msgid "We love to hear your thoughts and feedback on the products in this guide. And other users might like to join you in a conversation about any experiences or concerns you’ve had with a product. Please join the conversation in the comment section at the bottom of each product page."
msgstr "Nous sommes impatients de lire vos avis et vos commentaires sur les produits présentés dans ce guide. Et d’autres utilisateurs pourraient se joindre à vous pour discuter de vos expériences ou de vos préoccupations concernant un produit. Vous pouvez participer dans la section « Commentaires » au bas de chaque page produit."

#: network-api/networkapi/buyersguide/templates/about/how_to_use.html:326
